{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/technical/medium/2021-07-09_How-to-Build-a-Simple-ToDo-App-in-React-Native-using-Redux-Toolkit-eb9ca5409a1d/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Yajana Rao"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"3f137229-577b-51ef-800a-351a27fdbece","excerpt":"In this article, we will build a simple todo app using the Redux toolkit in React Native.  Link expo snack: https://snack.expo.io/@yajana/react-native-redux…","html":"<p>In this article, we will build a simple todo app using the Redux toolkit in React Native.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/a3aceddf1bbc5e283b32308640edcb75/5a190/1__6cxXyP9mA4BKd9Vf0QrleQ.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 56.75675675675676%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"1  6cxXyP9mA4BKd9Vf0QrleQ\"\n        title=\"1  6cxXyP9mA4BKd9Vf0QrleQ\"\n        src=\"/static/a3aceddf1bbc5e283b32308640edcb75/fcda8/1__6cxXyP9mA4BKd9Vf0QrleQ.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/a3aceddf1bbc5e283b32308640edcb75/12f09/1__6cxXyP9mA4BKd9Vf0QrleQ.png 148w,\n/static/a3aceddf1bbc5e283b32308640edcb75/e4a3f/1__6cxXyP9mA4BKd9Vf0QrleQ.png 295w,\n/static/a3aceddf1bbc5e283b32308640edcb75/fcda8/1__6cxXyP9mA4BKd9Vf0QrleQ.png 590w,\n/static/a3aceddf1bbc5e283b32308640edcb75/5a190/1__6cxXyP9mA4BKd9Vf0QrleQ.png 800w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><strong><em>Link expo snack:</em></strong> <a href=\"https://snack.expo.io/@yajana/react-native-redux-toolkit\"><em>https://snack.expo.io/@yajana/react-native-redux-toolkit</em></a></p>\n<p><strong><em>Link to GitHub repository:</em></strong> <a href=\"https://github.com/YajanaRao/react-native-redux-toolkit-app\"><em>https://github.com/YajanaRao/react-native-redux-toolkit-app</em></a></p>\n<p>Let’s start by installing the required libraries for building a todo app.</p>\n<h3>Install required dependencies</h3>\n<p>Install redux-toolkit using npm or yarn</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 452px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/fcb026997c77cff668444d03f1e2a747/fcb94/1__MDLcg99WBCOHPTV1JJHwAA.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 35.13513513513513%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"1  MDLcg99WBCOHPTV1JJHwAA\"\n        title=\"1  MDLcg99WBCOHPTV1JJHwAA\"\n        src=\"/static/fcb026997c77cff668444d03f1e2a747/fcb94/1__MDLcg99WBCOHPTV1JJHwAA.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/fcb026997c77cff668444d03f1e2a747/12f09/1__MDLcg99WBCOHPTV1JJHwAA.png 148w,\n/static/fcb026997c77cff668444d03f1e2a747/e4a3f/1__MDLcg99WBCOHPTV1JJHwAA.png 295w,\n/static/fcb026997c77cff668444d03f1e2a747/fcb94/1__MDLcg99WBCOHPTV1JJHwAA.png 452w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 452px) 100vw, 452px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3>Creating a Redux Store</h3>\n<p>Let’s start by creating a file named <code class=\"language-text\">src/store.js</code>. Import the <code class=\"language-text\">configureStore</code> API from Redux Toolkit. We’ll start by creating an empty Redux store, and exporting it:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 543px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/e09b85bbf5d2aed906dec3579cdefe24/29579/1__asYuPJCXt__R1l9apDL0q__g.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 28.37837837837838%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"1  asYuPJCXt  R1l9apDL0q  g\"\n        title=\"1  asYuPJCXt  R1l9apDL0q  g\"\n        src=\"/static/e09b85bbf5d2aed906dec3579cdefe24/29579/1__asYuPJCXt__R1l9apDL0q__g.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/e09b85bbf5d2aed906dec3579cdefe24/12f09/1__asYuPJCXt__R1l9apDL0q__g.png 148w,\n/static/e09b85bbf5d2aed906dec3579cdefe24/e4a3f/1__asYuPJCXt__R1l9apDL0q__g.png 295w,\n/static/e09b85bbf5d2aed906dec3579cdefe24/29579/1__asYuPJCXt__R1l9apDL0q__g.png 543w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 543px) 100vw, 543px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3>Provide the Redux Store to React Native</h3>\n<p>We will make the redux available to React Native components by wrapping React-Redux <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;Provider/></code> around our application in <code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code>. Import the Redux store we just created, put a <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;Provider/></code> around your <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;App/></code>, and pass the store as a prop:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/62f2d96edc5cb2e5938607002743274d/d8f62/1__wTfaFY4PNnbl2vqqMdaJKQ.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 57.432432432432435%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"1  wTfaFY4PNnbl2vqqMdaJKQ\"\n        title=\"1  wTfaFY4PNnbl2vqqMdaJKQ\"\n        src=\"/static/62f2d96edc5cb2e5938607002743274d/fcda8/1__wTfaFY4PNnbl2vqqMdaJKQ.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/62f2d96edc5cb2e5938607002743274d/12f09/1__wTfaFY4PNnbl2vqqMdaJKQ.png 148w,\n/static/62f2d96edc5cb2e5938607002743274d/e4a3f/1__wTfaFY4PNnbl2vqqMdaJKQ.png 295w,\n/static/62f2d96edc5cb2e5938607002743274d/fcda8/1__wTfaFY4PNnbl2vqqMdaJKQ.png 590w,\n/static/62f2d96edc5cb2e5938607002743274d/d8f62/1__wTfaFY4PNnbl2vqqMdaJKQ.png 601w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3><strong>Creating the Todos Slice</strong></h3>\n<p>Add a new file named <code class=\"language-text\">src/features/todos/todosSlice.js</code>. In that file, import the <code class=\"language-text\">createSlice</code> API from Redux Toolkit.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/b4beaf5cce33ee5e934cf8666c7a0b96/1f083/1__uPG69G0wod1qk__AnHzQ8__Q.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 74.32432432432432%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"1  uPG69G0wod1qk  AnHzQ8  Q\"\n        title=\"1  uPG69G0wod1qk  AnHzQ8  Q\"\n        src=\"/static/b4beaf5cce33ee5e934cf8666c7a0b96/fcda8/1__uPG69G0wod1qk__AnHzQ8__Q.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b4beaf5cce33ee5e934cf8666c7a0b96/12f09/1__uPG69G0wod1qk__AnHzQ8__Q.png 148w,\n/static/b4beaf5cce33ee5e934cf8666c7a0b96/e4a3f/1__uPG69G0wod1qk__AnHzQ8__Q.png 295w,\n/static/b4beaf5cce33ee5e934cf8666c7a0b96/fcda8/1__uPG69G0wod1qk__AnHzQ8__Q.png 590w,\n/static/b4beaf5cce33ee5e934cf8666c7a0b96/1f083/1__uPG69G0wod1qk__AnHzQ8__Q.png 660w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3><strong>Add Slice Reducers to the Store</strong></h3>\n<p>Next, we need to import the todos reducer function from the todos slice and add it to our store. By defining a field inside the reducers parameter, we tell the store to use this slice reducer function to handle all updates to that state.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 564px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ece84159982b78612f7322327b485547/ba4d9/1__MBldbjEu__Z0HQMrA0vsq9Q.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 35.13513513513513%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"1  MBldbjEu  Z0HQMrA0vsq9Q\"\n        title=\"1  MBldbjEu  Z0HQMrA0vsq9Q\"\n        src=\"/static/ece84159982b78612f7322327b485547/ba4d9/1__MBldbjEu__Z0HQMrA0vsq9Q.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ece84159982b78612f7322327b485547/12f09/1__MBldbjEu__Z0HQMrA0vsq9Q.png 148w,\n/static/ece84159982b78612f7322327b485547/e4a3f/1__MBldbjEu__Z0HQMrA0vsq9Q.png 295w,\n/static/ece84159982b78612f7322327b485547/ba4d9/1__MBldbjEu__Z0HQMrA0vsq9Q.png 564w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 564px) 100vw, 564px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3>Using Redux State and Actions in React Native Components</h3>\n<p>Now let’s create <code class=\"language-text\">AddTodo</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">TodoList</code> components to use redux state and actions.</p>\n<p>In AddTodo component, we use <code class=\"language-text\">useDispatch</code> to use Redux actions in React Native components. On pressing add button addTodo action will be dispatched with todo text as payload.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/227dde03232e6aa1b20823e0e2842e64/5a190/1__ZFy0aEbz30gp7ET7QUqVqQ.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 77.70270270270271%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"1  ZFy0aEbz30gp7ET7QUqVqQ\"\n        title=\"1  ZFy0aEbz30gp7ET7QUqVqQ\"\n        src=\"/static/227dde03232e6aa1b20823e0e2842e64/fcda8/1__ZFy0aEbz30gp7ET7QUqVqQ.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/227dde03232e6aa1b20823e0e2842e64/12f09/1__ZFy0aEbz30gp7ET7QUqVqQ.png 148w,\n/static/227dde03232e6aa1b20823e0e2842e64/e4a3f/1__ZFy0aEbz30gp7ET7QUqVqQ.png 295w,\n/static/227dde03232e6aa1b20823e0e2842e64/fcda8/1__ZFy0aEbz30gp7ET7QUqVqQ.png 590w,\n/static/227dde03232e6aa1b20823e0e2842e64/5a190/1__ZFy0aEbz30gp7ET7QUqVqQ.png 800w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>In TodoList we use <code class=\"language-text\">useSelector</code> hook to access the todos in the redux store.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3134125303405b6cd7ad5d210a6dc963/0f2bc/1__GHe511vXatZa9K5aZXfMXQ.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 93.91891891891892%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"1  GHe511vXatZa9K5aZXfMXQ\"\n        title=\"1  GHe511vXatZa9K5aZXfMXQ\"\n        src=\"/static/3134125303405b6cd7ad5d210a6dc963/fcda8/1__GHe511vXatZa9K5aZXfMXQ.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/3134125303405b6cd7ad5d210a6dc963/12f09/1__GHe511vXatZa9K5aZXfMXQ.png 148w,\n/static/3134125303405b6cd7ad5d210a6dc963/e4a3f/1__GHe511vXatZa9K5aZXfMXQ.png 295w,\n/static/3134125303405b6cd7ad5d210a6dc963/fcda8/1__GHe511vXatZa9K5aZXfMXQ.png 590w,\n/static/3134125303405b6cd7ad5d210a6dc963/0f2bc/1__GHe511vXatZa9K5aZXfMXQ.png 742w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Now let’s import <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;AddTodo/></code> and <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;TodoList/></code> component in App component to see a working Todo App.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Link expo snack</em></strong><em>:</em> <a href=\"https://snack.expo.io/@yajana/react-native-redux-toolkit\"><em>https://snack.expo.io/@yajana/react-native-redux-toolkit</em></a></p>\n<p><strong><em>Link to the GitHub repository</em></strong><em>:</em> <a href=\"https://github.com/YajanaRao/react-native-redux-toolkit-app\"><em>https://github.com/YajanaRao/react-native-redux-toolkit-app</em></a></p>\n<h4>References:</h4>\n<p><a href=\"https://redux-toolkit.js.org/tutorials/quick-start\">Redux Toolkit</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/reduxjs/redux-toolkit/blob/e85eb17b39a2118d859f7b7746e0f3fee523e089/docs/tutorials/intermediate-tutorial.md\">reduxjs/redux-toolkit</a></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to Build a Simple ToDo App in React Native using Redux Toolkit","date":"July 09, 2021","description":"In this article, we will build a simple todo app using the Redux toolkit in React Native."}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/technical/medium/2021-07-09_How-to-Build-a-Simple-ToDo-App-in-React-Native-using-Redux-Toolkit-eb9ca5409a1d/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/technical/medium/2021-06-27_Cross-platform-component-Libraries-in-React-Native-39fe78de3b61/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Cross platform component Libraries in React Native"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/technical/2021-07-13-using-react-native-why-did-you-render/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"How to use why did you render in react native"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["1105976633","1205699325","1246554614","2841359383","3336116537"]}